Quote:  Kowhaiwhai patterns have appeared on stamps, currency, and airline insignia but the breadth and complexity of this Maori art form has never been fully recognised... Traditionally, the art of kowhaiwhai painting was associated with the heke (rafters) of whare whakairo (carved ancestral meeting houses) and was the most highly developed form of Maori painting.
